<h2>Troubleshooting</h2>



<h3>Common Issues</h3>



<ol><li>**Authentication Failures**:</li></ol>

   - Verify that the token format is correct: <code>USER@REALM!TOKENID</code>

   - Ensure the token has appropriate permissions in Proxmox VE

   - Check that the token value is correct and not expired



<ol><li>**Connection Issues**:</li></ol>

   - Verify that the Proxmox server is reachable from the Comserv server

   - Check that the API URL is correct

   - Ensure that SSL verification is properly configured



<ol><li>**VM Creation Failures**:</li></ol>

   - Verify that the template URL is accessible from the Proxmox server

   - Check that the Proxmox server has sufficient resources

   - Ensure that the VM parameters are valid



<h3>Debugging</h3>



The Proxmox integration includes extensive logging to help diagnose issues:



<ol><li>**Controller Logging**: The Proxmox controller logs detailed information about user actions and API calls.</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Model Debugging**: The Proxmox model includes a debug_info hash with detailed information about API calls and responses.</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Connection Testing**: The ProxmoxServers controller includes a test_connection action that provides detailed diagnostics.</li></ol>



